{{wiktionary|Bug|bug}}

'''Bug''' may refer to:
{{tocright}}
==Biology==
* Formally, an insect of the order [[Hemiptera]], known as the "true bugs"
* Informally, an [[arthropod]]—except aquatic [[crustacean]]s and [[xiphosura]]—including individuals or species of
** [[insect]]
** [[arachnid]]
** [[myriapod]]
** [[woodlouse]]
** [[terrestrial crabs]]
* A strain of [[bacteria]], or any microorganism that causes illness or has a superficial resemblance to an insect or bug
* [[Bug (dog breed)]], a cross between a pug and a Boston terrier
* One of several species of [[slipper lobster]], such as
** [[Balmain bug]]
** [[Moreton Bay bug]]
* A [[trilobite]] called the [[Calymene blumenbachi|Dudley bug]].

==Locations==
* [[Bug (Rügen)]] in Germany
* [[Bug River]], in Ukraine, Poland, and Belarus
* [[Southern Bug]] River, in Ukraine
* [[Bug, Kentucky]]

==Technology==
* [[Covert listening device]], or bug, commonly used in espionage and in police investigations
* Nickname for various models of the [[Volkswagen Beetle]] automobile
* [[Software bug]] or hardware bug, a software or hardware defect
* [[Web bug]], a technique to track who has read a web page or e-mail
* [[Sandlin Bug]], a glider (sailplane) design

==Art and media==
===Characters===
* [[Bug (comics)]], a character in the Marvel comic book series ''The Micronauts''
* [[Bug (Starship Troopers)|Bug (''Starship Troopers'')]], a fictional alien race from the novel and film ''Starship Troopers''
* [[Bobby "Bug" Guthrie]], a character in the TV series ''Life Unexpected''

===In films and television===
* [[Bug (1975 film)|''Bug'' (1975 film)]], directed by Jeannot Szwarc
* [[Bug (2002 film)|''Bug'' (2002 film)]], a comedy-drama about a chain of events begun by a boy squashing a bug
* [[Bug (2006 film)|''Bug'' (2006 film)]], an adaptation of the Tracy Letts play, directed by William Friedkin
* [[Bug (Breaking Bad)|"Bug" (''Breaking Bad'')]], a 2011 television episode

===In gaming===
* [[Bug (poker)]], a restricted wild card
* ''[[Bug!]]'', a 1995 video game
* A [[holdout (gambling)]] device used for cheating in gambling

===In literature and publications===
* [[BUG (magazine)|''BUG'' (magazine)]], a Croatian magazine
* [[Bug (play)|''Bug'' (play)]], by Tracy Letts

===In music===
* [[Bug (soundtrack)|''Bug'' (soundtrack)]], the soundtrack to the film
* [[Bug (Dave Davies album)|''Bug'' (Dave Davies album)]]
* [[Bug (Dinosaur Jr. album)|''Bug'' (Dinosaur Jr. album)]]
* "Bug", a song by Phish from their 2000 album ''[[Farmhouse (album)]]''
* "Bug", a song by Feeder, from their album ''[[Echo Park (album)]]''
* "[[The Bug]]", a 1993 song by Dire Straits
* The Bug, a recording alias for UK musician [[Kevin Martin (British musician)|Kevin Martin]]

==People==
* [[Bug Hall]] (born 1985), American actor, acting teacher and musician
* [[Bug Holliday]] (1867–1910), baseball player

==Acronyms==
* [[Bicycle User Group]], a group set up to promote cycling issues
* [[Brooklyn Union Gas]], now known as KeySpan Corporation

==Other uses==
* [[Bug AS]], a full service production company based in Norway
* A distinctive logo or symbol, such as a watermark-like [[digital on-screen graphic]] of a broadcaster's logo or a [[union label]]
* [[Buginese language]], ISO 639 code "bug"

